The paper discusses the development of a compiler that supports productivity, portability, and performance simultaneously, which is a topic that falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks for performance prediction suggests that the paper may also belong to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions Halide implementations, which is a domain-specific language for image processing and computational photography, indicating that it may also belong to the computer graphics (cs.AR) sub-category.
